It will be more visible that one of them has only to_json and other one from_json
As this way of serialization is not supported in bmcweb, I decided to remove those types and functions.

It's not that it's not supported, it's that it requires throwing exceptions, which are generally not caught in bmcweb, as 99% of errors in bmcweb are "recoverable" by simply returning an error code or closing the connection.
Why array_t instead of array?
